
The files "1", "2", "4" have the datapoints needed for gnu plotting.
To run aloha.cpp use the make command and run is as ./a.out -N 50 -W 2 -p 0.5 -M 5000

Note that every iteration is being shown including the buffer and backoffs in the stdout.
In case you wish to see only the throughput and average packet delay, please comment out
the "cout" functions in the code. 
